<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 24 at 11:18AM CST  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Searcy,
southeastern Newton, northwestern Van Buren and northeastern Pope
Counties through 1145 AM CST...
At 1116 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Solo, or 24 miles north of Russellville, moving northeast at 75 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail and heavy freezing rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Heavy freezing
rain will produce additional ice accumulation.
Locations impacted include...
Marshall...                       Marsena...
Kay...                            Bohannon...
Woolum...                         Imo...
Witts Spring...                   Rocky Hill...
Moore...                          Elberta...
Smyrna...                         Watts...
Leslie...                         Ben Hur...
Canaan...                         Silver Hill...
Chimes...                         Nogo...
Snowball...                       Tilly...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
